close_reason: Adopted ids.token_length 6 in the repository settings.json as a minimal 3-line sparse diff (full-default materialization from the config-set round-trip deliberately reverted and filed as pm-x2aplf); rationale and birthday-bound table live in MERGE_SAFETY.md.
body: "## Context\nPR#617 (pm-pibw) made id entropy configurable and its migration guidance explicitly recommends `ids.token_length 6` for multi-agent/branch repositories. This repository is the flagship multi-agent fan-out workspace (parallel maintainer/codex/pi lanes branching between merges) yet still runs the default token_length 4 (~184 concurrent unsynced creations for a 1% birthday collision). pm-iwsj adopted the merge-safety contract but did not cover entropy.\n\n## Change\n`pm config set project ids.token_length 6` (2.18B id space, ~6.6k concurrent unsynced creations at 1%). Existing 4-char ids stay valid; only newly minted ids grow."
